the usual brutality exercised(581,10)ship:(1497,8)never believed it to b(1718,8)ary, and when I heard of a mariner equally noted(481,9)kindliness
of heart(490,9)respect and obedience paid to him by his crew, I felt
myself peculiarly fortunate in being able to secure his services.(191,8)
of him first in rather a(1567,9) manner, from a lady who owes(164,8)the
happi(693,9)er life. This, briefly, is his story. Some years ago he loved
a young Russian lady of moderate fortune, and having amassed a considerable
