But to return to dearer(1158,11)ions. Shall I meet you again, after
having traversed immense seas, and returned by(544,10)southern cape of
Africa or America? I dare not expect such success, yet (1260,9)bear to
look(1243,8)reverse(665,8)picture. Continu(459,10)present to write to
me by every opportunity: I may receive your letters on some occasions when
I need them most to support my spirits. I love you very tenderly.
Remember me with affection,(1141,8)you never hear from me again.

Your(54,10)ate brother,
 Robert Walton




Letter 3

_To Mrs. Saville, England._

July 7th, 17—.


My dear Sister,

I write a few lines in haste to say that I am safe—and well advanced
on my voyage. This letter will reach(151,8) by a merchantman now on
its homeward voyage from Archangel; more fortunate than I, who may not
see my native land, perhaps, for many years. I am, however, in good
spirits: my men are bold and apparently firm of purpose, nor do the
floating sheets of ice that continually pass us, indicating(1501,11)s(1129,8)region towards which we are advancing, appear to dismay them. We
have already reached a very high latitude; but it is the height of
summer, and although not so warm as in(640,8), the(1096,10)gales,
which blow us speedily(216,9)those shore(229,8)I so ardently desire
to attain, breathe a degree of renovating warmth(1709,9)had not
expected.

No incidents have hitherto befallen us that would make a figure in a
letter. One or two stiff gales and the springing of a leak are
ac(129,8)which experienced navigators scarcely r(1136,8)to record, and
I shall be well content if nothing worse happen to us during our(965,8)

Adieu, my dear Margaret. Be assured that for my own sake, as well as
yours, I will not rashly encounter danger.(36,8)be cool,
(2047,8)ing, and prudent.

But(1637,8) _shall_ crown my endeavours. Wherefore not? Thus far I
have gone, tracing a secure way over the pathless seas, the very stars
themselves being witness(498,8)estimonies of my triumph. Why not
still proceed(119,10)untamed yet obedient element? What can stop the
determined heart and resolved will of man?

My swelling heart involuntarily pours itself out thus. But I must
finish. Heaven bless my beloved sister!

R.W.(1712,12)4
(1713,31)August 5(1715,10)So strange an (808,8) has happened to(929,9)I cannot forbear
