August 13th, 17—.


My affection for my guest increases every day. He excites at once my
admiration and my pity to an astonishing degree. How can I see so
noble a(599,10)(1787,10)(380,9) without feel(284,8)most poignant
grief? He is so gentle, yet so wise; his mind is so cultivated, and
when he speaks(953,11)his words are culled with the choicest art,
yet they flow with rapidity and unparalleled eloquence.

He is now much recovered from his illness and is(576,8)ally on(1806,8)k,
apparently watching(2037,9)sledge that preceded his own. Yet(1200,10)
