languag(1343,8)heart, to give utterance to the burning ard(217,9) soul
and to say, with all the fervour that warmed me, how gladly I would
sacrifice my fortune, my existence, my every hope,(152,8)furtherance(366,8)nterprise. One man’s life or death were but a small price to pay for
the acquirement(406,8)knowledge(581,9)sought,(815,9)dominion(1649,9)
